## Target Architecture: 13-Stage Deep Pipeline

Every user query flows through all 13 stages as LangGraph nodes. Intent classification at stage 3 determines *how* downstream stages behave (prompt selection, retrieval corpus, guardrail strictness), not which stages run.

```
User
  │
  ▼
① Authentication          ─ API key / JWT validation
  │
  ▼
② Query Validation        ─ Length, PII, language, abuse detection
  │
  ▼
③ Intent Classification   ─ Route: rag | debug | codegen | concept
  │
  ▼
④ Query Rewriting         ─ Expand, disambiguate, multi-query generation
  │
  ▼
⑤ Hybrid Retrieval        ─ Vector (ChromaDB) + BM25 → merged results
  │              └──────── User-doc namespace search (Enterprise)
  │              └──────── Tavily web fallback (if KB score < threshold)
  ▼
⑥ Re-ranking              ─ Cross-score fusion, MMR diversity filter
  │
  ▼
⑦ Context Compression     ─ Trim to token budget, summarize stale chunks
  │
  ▼
⑧ Hallucination Check     ─ Pre-generation: "Can context support an answer?"
  │
  ▼
⑨ Answer Generation       ─ Intent-specific prompts, conversation history injected
  │
  ▼
⑩ Citation Verification   ─ Verify answer cites real source IDs from context
  │
  ▼
⑪ Safety / Guardrails     ─ Toxic content, off-topic, injection detection
  │
  ▼
⑫ Logging & Observability ─ Structured log per stage, latency, token counts
  │
  ▼
⑬ User Feedback Loop      ─ Tag response ID for async thumbs up/down
  │
  ▼
Streaming Response (SSE)
```

