### Phase 4 — Enterprise Document Upload Feature

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is the key enterprise differentiator — users can upload their own codebases, docs, or README files and ask questions about *their specific project*, in addition to the global Stack Overflow KB.

#### [NEW] `app/upload/processor.py`
Supported formats: **PDF, DOCX, TXT, MD, PY**
- `pypdf2` for PDF extraction
- `python-docx` for DOCX
- Raw text for TXT/MD/PY
- Cleans, chunks, embeds using existing `HuggingFaceEmbeddings`
- Returns `list[Document]` with metadata `{source: filename, user_id, doc_id}`

#### [NEW] `app/upload/namespace.py`
- Creates per-user ChromaDB collection: `user_docs_{user_id}`
- `add_documents(user_id, docs)` → index to user namespace
- `search_user_docs(user_id, query, k=5)` → retrieval from user namespace
- `list_user_docs(user_id)` → document metadata list
- `delete_document(user_id, doc_id)` → remove from collection

#### New API Endpoints for Upload:
```
POST   /upload                 — Upload document (PDF/DOCX/TXT/MD/PY)
GET    /documents              — List my uploaded documents
DELETE /documents/{doc_id}     — Delete a document
GET    /documents/{doc_id}/chunks — Preview indexed chunks
```

